OL,3,CReform UK takes control of Newcastle-
OL,4,Cunder-Lyme borough
OL,6,FElsewhere in the Midlands, Reform also
OL,7,Fmade huge gains in Dudley, becoming
OL,8,Fthe second largest party there. The
OL,9,FConservative held onto control of
OL,10,FDudley Council, which only had a third
OL,11,Fof its seats up for election.
OL,13,FIn Redditch, Labour lost its majority,
OL,14,Fwith Reform taking eight of the nine
OL,15,Fseats being contested there. There's
OL,16,Fnow no party majority in the council.
OL,18,FIn Tamworth, Labour is still the
OL,19,Flargest party but has lost overall
OL,20,Fcontrol, with Reform winning all seats
OL,21,Fbeing contested.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/5
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
